   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Resource Efficient and Cleaner Production Programme in Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In January of 2016, the PTC Managing Director (PTC-MD) traveled on an official mission to Nigeria. The aim of the mission was to consolidate the partnership/collaboration between Nigeria#s focal and counterpart ministry to UNIDO - Federal Ministry of Industry, Trade and Investment (FMITI) and other relevant Ministries, Department and Agencies (MDAs) at the federal and state levels. The PTC-MD met and presented UNIDO#s global programmes and continued commitments to Federal Ministers of responsible for the; Ministry of Industry, Trade and Investment, Ministry of Science and Technology, Ministry of Water Resources and Rural Development, Ministry of Power, Works and Housing, Ministry of  Agriculture, and Ministry of Environment. And the Manufacturers Association of Nigeria During discussions with the Minister of Environment, Ms. Amina Mohammed, (now UN Deputy Secretary General) took note of the broad cooperation developed between UNIDO and her Ministry when helping Nigeria meet its obligations under various multilateral environment agreements (MP, POPs), but also in areas such a renewable energy, waste management, and resource efficient and cleaner production. Of special interest to the Minister Ms. Amina are a review of the regulatory environment, its effectiveness and adequacy in modern times. In this regards, UN</narrative>
  </description>
